<title>USA: Roy F. Weston sees &quot;substantial&quot; Q2 loss.</title>
<headline>Roy F. Weston sees &quot;substantial&quot; Q2 loss.</headline>
<dateline>WEST CHESTER, Pa. 1997-05-23</dateline>
<text>
<p>Roy F. Weston Inc, an environmental services firm, said on Friday that it anticipates a second quarter loss due to weakness in the company's industrial sector.</p>
<p>The extent of the company's loss could not be determined, but the company said it is &quot;expected that it may be substantial.&quot;</p>
<p>In last year's second quarter, the company reported a loss of $0.07 a share, or $670,000, on revenues of $46.3 million.</p>
